Package: genoformerR
Type: Package
Title: Ancestry-Aware Polygenic Risk Scoring via Transformer (GenoFormer)
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Shu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "user@example.com")
Description: R wrapper for GenoFormer — a transformer-based ancestry-aware
    polygenic risk scoring pipeline using 1000 Genomes Phase 3 as ancestry
    reference. Provides functions for genotype QC, haplotype phasing (SHAPEIT4),
    local ancestry inference (RFMix2), per-SNP local ancestry conditioning in the
    transformer, global ancestry inference via PCA, model training and inference,
    PRS computation, and cross-ancestry portability evaluation. Handles admixed
    cohorts via dual-level conditioning: global ancestry (FiLM per block) and
    local ancestry (per-SNP token embedding). Python backend (PyTorch) is managed
    via reticulate.
